library(ggplot2)
library(astsa)
library(dplyr)
library(xts)

1 EXERCISE 1

1.1 Question 1

\[X_t=X_{t_1}+\epsilon_t,\quad X_0=0\]

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
X=numeric()
X[1]=0
n<-500
for (k in 2:n) 
{
  X[k]=X[k-1]+rnorm(1)
}

plot.ts(X,col='steel blue',frame=FALSE)
acf(ts(X))

## Question 2

diffX<-diff(X)
plot.ts(diffX,col='steel blue',frame=FALSE)

There is no trend and the autocorrelation is nearly zero.

acf(diffX)

2 EXERCISE 2

\[Y_t=0.25+0.75Y_{t-1}+\epsilon_t\]

2.1 Question 1

Y=numeric()
Y[1]=0
print(Y)
[1] 0
for (k in 2:n)
{
  Y[k]=0.25+0.75*Y[k-1]+rnorm(1)
}

plot.ts(Y,col='steel blue',frame=FALSE)

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
acf(ts(Y))
pacY<-pacf(Y)

3 EXERCISE 3

3.1 Question 1

\[X_t=Z(t)+0.75Z(t-1)\quad,Z\approx\mathcal{N}(0,1)\]

set.seed(123)
Z<-rnorm(n+1)
X<-numeric()
for (k in 2:(n+1))
{
    X[k]=Z[k]+0.75*Z[k-1]
}
X<-X[-1]
X1<-stats::filter(rnorm(n+1),filter=c(1,0.75),method='convolution')
X1<-X1[-1]
plot(ts(X),col='steel blue',frame=FALSE)

#lines(ts(X1),col='red')
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
acf(X)
pacf(X)
